        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 12:12AM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 1212 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles southeast of Amory, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Vernon, Sulligent, Detroit, Beaverton, Blooming Grove, Lamar County
Airport, Crews, Bedford, Crossville, Gattman, Cody, Lamar County
Public Lake, and Pine Springs.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
